
1) Fetch list of users from Mailman (WWW::Mailman)
2) Send e-mail directly to each person. Reduce the use of Mailman only for managing subscriptions.
3) Create a redirection script that will get a unique URL and redirect the 
   user to the real URL logging the requests.
4) When generating the e-mail messages replace the real links with 
   unique links pointing to counter created in 3)
5) Create subscription management in Dwimmer 
6) Move the whole thing over to use Dwimmer.


*) add RSS and Atom feed for the feed junkies?


